WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.120
Do you have a chunk of code you really need to show or a chunk of text?

00:00:04.480 --> 00:00:08.000
Quarto is my favorite tool for technical communications. Here's a quick Quarto tip

00:00:08.000 --> 00:00:13.360
for making great presentation slides. Maybe you need to emphasize a bit of that code or text for

00:00:13.360 --> 00:00:18.719
a class or for a presentation. Quarto slides give you a bunch of options that help you emphasize

00:00:18.719 --> 00:00:23.360
different parts of a slide. You have code chunk animation that lets you reveal new bits of code

00:00:23.360 --> 00:00:28.000
within your chunk. You can highlight a bit of code or text with a little bit of styling like color.

00:00:28.000 --> 00:00:31.520
There's also a bunch of slide fragment options including highlighting with color,

00:00:31.520 --> 00:00:36.959
easing in, easing out, and more. This might all seem like a small trivial set of features,

00:00:36.959 --> 00:00:41.520
but these kind of highlighting options make for good presentation and good teaching practice.

00:00:41.520 --> 00:00:46.160
There aren't so many distractions in the classroom or in the meeting room or in the Zoom room.

00:00:46.160 --> 00:00:50.560
Help your audience know where to look. Highlight or emphasize exactly where you are and what you're

00:00:50.560 --> 00:00:55.759
talking about. This helps make a more engaging bit of technical communication. Follow for more

00:00:55.759 --> 00:00:58.000
free and open source data science tips.

